  "prompt": "How was Ankara chosen to be the capital of Turkey?",
  "response": "Ankara was chosen to be the capital of Turkey in 1923. The decision was made by Mustafa Kemal Atat\u00fcrk, the founder and first president of the Republic of Turkey, as part of his efforts to modernize and secularize the country following the fall of the Ottoman Empire.\n\nThere were several reasons for choosing Ankara over Istanbul, which had been the capital of the Ottoman Empire. These include:\n\n1. **Geographical Location**: Ankara is located in the interior of the country, which made it less vulnerable to foreign attacks compared to Istanbul, situated on the coast. Its central location also facilitated better administration and communication across the new republic.\n\n2. **Symbol of Change**: Atat\u00fcrk wanted to signify a break from the Ottoman past and the establishment of a new, modern republic. Moving the capital to Ankara was a symbolic gesture to represent this new beginning.\n\n3. **Strategic Importance**: During the Turkish War of Independence, Ankara served as the headquarters for Atat\u00fcrk and the nationalist movement. Its role during the war demonstrated its strategic importance.\n\n4. **Development Potential**: Atat\u00fcrk saw Ankara as a place with great potential for development. Unlike Istanbul, which was already heavily populated and burdened with the legacies of the Ottoman Empire, Ankara provided a blank slate for new governmental and administrative buildings.\n\nBy making Ankara the capital, Atat\u00fcrk aimed to create a new Turkish identity and foster a sense of unity and progress in the country. The official declaration of Ankara as the capital took place on October 13, 1923, shortly before the proclamation of the Republic of Turkey on October 29, 1923.",
